<p><strong>UK Music Sales Buoyant</strong></p>
<p><em>[BBC]</em></p>
<p>The BPI reports that a total of <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-35234297">26.8bn songs were streamed in the UK last year</a>, a rise of 82%.&nbsp; Vinyl sales jumped 64% to 2.1 million, while retailer HMV says it sold a turntable every minute over Christmas.&nbsp; However, plastic remains the dominant format, with 53.6m CDs and 119.6m DVD and Blu-Ray discs sold last year.</p>
