<p>As four new elements are about to be added to the periodic table, 100,000 people have signed a petition to have one of the new heavy metals named after recently-deceased <a href="http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/01/08/462368064/put-lemmy-on-the-periodic-table-more-than-100-000-sign-petition">Mot&ouml;rhead frontman, Lemmy</a>.</p>
