<li>
<p>ECU has released guidance on <a href="http://www.ecu.ac.uk/guidance-resources/student-recruitment-retention-attainment/student-retention/inclusive-learning-teaching/competence-standards-reasonable-adjustments/">Understanding the interaction of competence standards and reasonable adjustments</a>.&nbsp; [Annie Bryan]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Catherine Chambers looks at <a href="https://catherinechambersthinkvisual.wordpress.com/2015/10/29/building-a-learning-community-through-live-broadcast/">live vs on-demand broadcasting</a> and the impact of Google Hangouts on a recent FL MOOC.&nbsp; [Catherine Chambers]&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/11/10/offline-navigation-comes-to-google-maps/?ncid=tcdaily#.vlxkaj:vsTS">Google Maps</a> now offers offline navigation and search, initially for Android but with iOS to follow.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Glasgow Caledonian&rsquo;s <a href="http://www.gcu.ac.uk/library/pilot/">PILOT information literacy training resource</a>, is up and running, and mobile friendly.&nbsp; [Beccy Dresden]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The <a href="http://www.irrodl.org/index.php/irrodl/issue/view/70">latest issue of IRRODL</a> has papers on m-learning, open access, social media, dropout rates and much more.&nbsp; [IRRODL]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/10/13/two-new-apps-tackle-the-problem-of-running-out-of-space-on-your-phone">Struggling for space on your 8 or 16GB iPhone</a>?&nbsp; Sarah Perez looks at two apps (&lsquo;Ice Cream&rsquo; and &lsquo;Room for More&rsquo;) that could help.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The EC is to invest almost <a href="http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=20151014005138294">&euro;16 billion in research and innovation</a> in 2016/17 under its Horizon 2020 programme.&nbsp; [University World News]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Phil Hill provides a nice graphical summary of <a href="http://mfeldstein.com/state-of-the-us-higher-education-lms-market-2015-edition/">the state of the US HE LMS/VLE market</a>.&nbsp; [Audrey Watters]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The 2016 <a href="http://bufvc.ac.uk/events/learningonscreen?utm_content=bufferc0881&utm_medium=social&utm_source=twitter.com&utm_campaign=buffer">Learning on Screen Awards</a> are now open for entries.&nbsp; [BUFVC]</p>
</li>
<li>
