</li>
<li>
<p>Twitter will next month <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/06/11/twitter-gets-serious-about-messaging-will-remove-dm-character-limit/?ncid=rss&utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed:+Techcrunch+(TechCrunch)#.kaibxm:iNeT">remove the 140 character limit on direct messaging</a>.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-33076520">Vodafone</a> is entering the UK home broadband market in selected areas, with preferential rates for existing customers.&nbsp; [BBC]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tenders are invited (by 6 Jul) for <a href="http://et-foundation.mytenders.org/Search/Show/Search_View.aspx?ID=JUN110031">delivery of learning and development opportunities in the education and training sector</a>.&nbsp; [ALT]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/06/08/itunes-app-store-passes-1-5m-apps-100b-downloads-30b-paid-to-developers/">Apple&rsquo;s App Store</a> now offers 1.5 million apps, has passed 100bn downloads and paid over $30bn to developers.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Oxford&rsquo;s last remaining all-male college, <a href="http://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/06/04/uk-women-university-oxford-idUKKBN0OK1YB20150604">St Benet's Hall, will open its doors to women</a>.&nbsp; Although not for weepy science subjects, obviously...&nbsp; [Reuters]</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</p>
<p><strong>And Finally&hellip;</strong></p>
<p><em>[Rafa Hidalgo]</em></p>
<p>360 deg videos have been around for a while now but YouTube launched its 360 player back in March.&nbsp; The technology is aimed mainly at the growing VR market (Oculus Rift, Google Cardboard, etc) but the videos work well on iPads and Android tablets, where you can swipe or simply move your device around to see left, right, up and down.&nbsp; Search within YouTube for &ldquo;360 videos&rdquo; or you might want to check out the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t99N223fqCo">wingsuit flying experience</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uHsCeJD4nBc">Okinawa underwater</a>, or some of the rides at <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hgE120RX5Hs">Parc Asterix</a>.</p>
