<li>
<p><a href="http://venturebeat.com/2015/03/14/30-years-of-com-domains/">The world&rsquo;s first &ldquo;dot com&rdquo; domain name</a> (Symbolics.com) was born 30 years ago this month.&nbsp; [VentureBeat]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The OU has been awarded &pound;2.7m from HEFCE to build on the success of OSL and develop the <a href="http://www3.open.ac.uk/media/fullstory.aspx?MEDIA=tw100nscimr_628&LKCAMPAIGN=tw100&id=28618">OpenSTEM Laboratory</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Apple has raised the <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/02/12/ios-app-size-limit/?ncid=tcdaily">maximum file size of an iOS app</a> from 2GB to 4GB.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You can now <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/03/12/google-partners-with-local-nonprofit-to-bring-street-view-better-maps-to-mount-everest-region">explore the Mount Everest region</a> of Nepal via Google Street View.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>TeachThought offers <a href="http://www.teachthought.com/technology/50-animation-tools-resources-digital-learners">50 animation tools and resources</a> for digital learners and educators.&nbsp; [TeachThought]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Scientists have identified the part of the brain teachers use to <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/education-31503265">detect when pupils do not understand</a> what they are being taught.&nbsp; [BBC]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Interesting eleven-page <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/edit?id=1TQupkuKAo7HQT-Sc8wMOcqVvXtc9j4QGWA2BrfBWpbI&hl=en">A-Z list of Google tools and projects</a>, from Aardvark through to Zeitgeist.&nbsp; [Stephen Downes]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Apple is going to allow educational system admins to <a href="http://www.theverge.com/2015/3/8/8170205/apple-will-make-it-easier-for-schools-to-use-ipads-by-dropping-apple">download apps and content to shared iPads</a> without requiring an Apple ID.&nbsp; [The Verge]</p>
