<li>Serhiy Kvit, <a href="http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=20140311231130571">Ukraine's new Minister of Education and Science</a>, gives his perspective on the current situation.&nbsp; [University World News]</li>
<li>In a mock poll held at Glasgow Caledonian University, <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/03/11/glasgow-students-vote-against-scottish-independence_n_4940911.html?ir=UK+Universities+&+Education">63% of students voted in favour of keeping Scotland as part of the UK</a>.&nbsp; [Huffington Post]</li>
<li>An interesting definition of <a href="http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=20140212134833693">exam cheating</a> from cuddly old China: it now amounts to &ldquo;illegal acquisition of state secrets&rdquo;.&nbsp; [University World News]</li>
<li>BBC Panorama uncovers the extent of organised <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-26024375">fraud in UK visa application process English tests</a> run by Studentway.&nbsp; [BBC]</li>
<li>Mikhail Panko&rsquo;s <a href="http://www.expresso-app.org/">Expresso</a> is a free web tool that analyses the construction of written text and flags weaknesses.&nbsp; [makeuseof.com]</li>
<li><a href="http://campustechnology.com/articles/2014/02/26/new-openid-connect-standard-extends-digital-identities-across-the-web.aspx">OpenID Connect</a> is a new standard for internet security and privacy just ratified by the OpenID Foundation.&nbsp; [Campus Technology]</li>
<li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/mar/07/photographers-getty-images">Getty</a> is allowing social media users to freely embed almost any of its 30m images on sites such as Twitter and WordPress.&nbsp; [The Guardian]</li>
<li>Dropbox users may appreciate these seven downloads and extensions &ldquo;to <a href="http://lifehacker.com/seven-downloads-and-extensions-to-make-dropbox-even-mor-1533124676">make Dropbox even more awesome</a>&rdquo;.&nbsp; [Lifehacker]</li>
<li><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2014/03/11/google-docs-add-ons/">Google Docs</a> now has an add-on store, with 60+ productivity extensions currently available.&nbsp; [Engadget]</li>
<li>UCAS made &pound;12m last year by <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/mar/12/ucas-sells-marketing-access-student-data-advertisers">selling applicants&rsquo; and parents&rsquo; data</a> to advertisers such as mobile phone and energy drinks companies.&nbsp; [The Guardian]</li>
<li>The <a href="http://mashable.com/2014/03/13/first-cellphone-on-sale/">world&rsquo;s first mobile phone went on sale 30 years ago</a> this month.&nbsp; The Motorola DynaTAC 8000X was a snip at just $3995.&nbsp; [Mashable]</li>
<li><a href="http://ilearntechnology.com/?p=5286">Stormboard</a> is a virtual brainstorming, mindmapping and collaboration tool that lets teams share online whiteboard space.&nbsp; [iLearn Technology]</li>
</ul>
