<li>Med Kharbach suggests <a href="http://www.educatorstechnology.com/2013/11/7-wonderful-ipad-apps-to-learn-about.html">7 iPad apps to learn about human body in 3D</a>.&nbsp; [Educators Technology]</li>
<li>The BBC aims to support a new generation of programmers by making <a href="http://www.agent4change.net/events/event/2121-bbc-makes-2015-year-of-making-and-coding.html">2015 a year of &lsquo;making and coding&rsquo;</a>.&nbsp; [MJO]</li>
<li>Gordon Ritter suggests that education (along with healthcare) stand out as the most <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2013/10/26/are-you-in-a-cloud-friendly-industry/">cloud-friendly industries</a>.&nbsp; [Matthew Moran]</li>
</ul>
<p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</p>
<p><strong>And Finally&hellip;</strong></p>
<p><em>[TechCrunch]</em></p>
<p>Launched on 29 Oct, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DtyfiPIHsIg">Virgin America&rsquo;s new flight safety video</a> has already generated nearly 6m YouTube views.&nbsp; Considering most people&rsquo;s natural aversion to the subject matter, it&rsquo;s a masterpiece.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Tue, 12 Nov 2013 13:17:52 +0000</pubDate>
            </item>
                    <item>
              <title>e-Learning Digest No 110 - Oct 13</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8499</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8499</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>UK </strong><strong>Conferences &amp; Workshops </strong></p>
