              <title>e-Learning Digest No 77 - Jan 11</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4974</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4974</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Don't Lecture Me</strong></p>
<p><em>[ALT]</em></p>
<p>Donald Clark's ALT-C keynote speech caused controversy at the time, and has been viewed over 3,000 times on <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/ClipsFromALT#p/c/ACF99396D1EF7393/3/Tbl-xXF8NPY">ALT's YouTube channel</a>.&nbsp; As a result, Donald will be running a <a href="http://tinyurl.com/288lkvh">free lunchtime webinar</a> focusing on 'evidence' that unrecorded lectures, rather than being a proven pedagogic method, fail the learner.&nbsp; The webinar will be run using Elluminate, starting at 12 noon on <strong>Tue 18 Jan</strong> and followed by a facilitated open discussion, with the whole session lasting approximately 1 hour.</p>
<p>~~~~~~~~</p>
<p><strong>UK </strong><strong>Conferences &amp; Workshops </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>3 Feb, Birmingham, <a href="http://www.jisc.ac.uk/assessworkshops">Effective Assessment in a Digital Age</a>.&nbsp; [ALT]</li>
<li>15 Feb, London, <a href="http://insidegovernment.msgfocus.com/c/1LINP7jcMuTSvKFfN">Widening Participation: Unleashing Aspiration and Fulfilling Potential in HE</a>. [ALT]</li>
<li>15 Feb, Leicester, <a href="http://www.niace.org.uk/campaigns-events/events/free-and-open-educational-resources">NIACE workshop: Free and Open Educational Resources</a>.&nbsp; [ALT]</li>
<li>17 Feb, London, <a href="http://www.neilstewartassociates.com/jd242/">FE-HE Collaboration: Drivers of Change</a>.&nbsp; [Neil Stewart Associates]</li>
<li>25 Feb, London, <a href="http://www.elearningnetwork.org/events/proven-recipes-elearning-success">Proven recipes for e-learning success</a>.&nbsp; [eLN]</li>
<li>1 Mar, London, <a href="http://www.lsis.org.uk/Services/Events/Pages/LSISresearchconference2011.aspx">Learning and Skills Improvement Service Research Conference 2011</a>.&nbsp; [ALT]</li>
